article.description: — Matt Cross scored 12 points to help Massachusetts defeat Charlotte 60-54 in the Myrtle Beach Invitational on Sunday.
article.headline: Cross helps UMass turn back Charlotte 60-54
article.linkText: Cross helps UMass turn back Charlotte 60-54
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. -- — Matt Cross scored 12 points to help Massachusetts defeat Charlotte 60-54 in the Myrtle Beach Invitational on Sunday. Cross was 5-of-7 shooting (2 for 3 from distance) for the Minutemen (4-1). T.J. Weeks added 11 points and nine rebounds. RJ Luis scored nine with six boards. Aly Khalifa led the 49ers (4-1) in scoring, finishing with 12 points. Igor Milicic Jr. added 11 points, while Brice Williams scored nine. Cross put up 10 points in the first half for UMass, which led 38-28 at halftime. NEXT UP UMass plays Tuesday against South Florida on the road, and Charlotte visits Detroit Mercy on Wednesday.
